hopobject.body: Have you got a telephone directory? primamed.com.tr If you assume you're safe because study conditions tend to be fairly extreme, think again. People who regularly get less than the optimum amount of sleep have been observed to eat 200 to 500 more calories per day than people who do not. "You prefer different foods, more of them, and at the wrong time of day," Buxton says. "Nobody is eating a salad in the middle of the night."
